  "text": "The development of therapeutic strategies to inhibit function of FOXO1 has been stimulated by research conducted on the crucial role of FOXO1 in metabolic disorders such as diabetes and obesity. Specific FOXO1 inhibitor AS1842856 has been developed and administered in vivo to diabetic or to asthmatic mice for short period of time. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] However, long-term in vivo studies using this inhibitor are lacking, and most studies were limited to in vitro applications so far. Importantly, our studies suggest that pharmacological inhibition of either PTEN or FOXO1 activity could be beneficial for patients with low CD20 levels on tumor cells, as both inhibitors upregulate surface levels of CD20 antigen.",
